20alt%3D%5C%22two%20similar%20looking%20websites%20are%20seen%20side%20by%20side%3A%20a%20fake%20USPS%20site%20and%20the%20real%20one%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e679424a32f30019748cb0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECan%20you%20spot%20the%20differences%20between%20the%20two%20websites%3F%20The%20fake%20one%20is%20on%20the%20left%20and%20the%20real%20one%20is%20on%20the%20right.%3Cp%3EInsider%3B%20USPS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20opened%20the%20link%20on%20my%20phone.%20I%20was%20suspicious.%20I%20then%20opened%20it%20on%20my%20laptop%20so%20I%20could%20click%20around%20and%20make%20sure%20it%20was%20actually%20the%20USPS.%20I%20am%20a%20prudent%20internet%20user%2C%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seemed%20legit.%20It%20linked%20to%20a%20page%20about%20%26quot%3Binformed%20delivery%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20%3Cem%3Eam%3C%2Fem%3E%20an%20Informed%20Delivery%20subscriber.%20I%20like%20to%20know%20when%20my%20late-night%20Halloween%20decor%20purchases%20are%20arriving%20before%20they%20hit%20my%20doorstep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20had%20a%20tracking%20number%2C%20an%20FAQ%20page%2C%20and%20other%20indicators%20that%20left%20me%20satisfied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20back%20to%20my%20phone%2C%20entered%20my%20home%20address%20%E2%80%94%20which%20in%20retrospect%20I'm%20not%20sure%20why%20they'd%20need%20that%20%E2%80%94%20my%20email%20address%2C%20and%20my%20phone%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20red%20flag%20that%20trumps%20all%20red%20flags%20appeared%3A%20it%20asked%20me%20for%20my%20credit%20card%20information%20for%20a%20%24o.30%20redelievery%20fee.%20I%20thought%20%E2%80%94%20this%20doesn't%20feel%20right%2C%20but%20what%20the%20hell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWELP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it%20prompted%20me%20to%20enter%20the%20verification%20code%20it%20sent%20to%20my%20phone.%20It%20also%20had%20a%20timer%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20