0355915%2FBest-ever-photograph-of-Loch-Ness-monster-revealed-as-a-fake.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephoto%20was%20an%20elaborate%20hoax%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20weekend%2C%20200%20monster%20hunters%20are%20trying%20to%20do%20what%20those%20before%20them%20failed%20to%20accomplish%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F08%2F26%2Floch-ness-monster-hunt-scotland%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20descending%20on%20the%20Highlands%20better%20equipped%20than%20their%20predecessors%2C%20using%20flying%20and%20underwater%20drones%20to%20survey%20the%20lake%2C%20which%20is%20788%20feet%20deep%20and%2023%20miles%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20also%20employing%20infrared%20cameras%20to%20determine%20heat%20spots%20and%20a%20hydrophone%20that%20can%20pick%20up%20acoustic%20signals%2060%20feet%20below%20the%20loch's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20not%20just%20people%20%26quot%3Bwith%20binoculars%20and%20a%20tub%20of%20sandwiches%2C%26quot%3B%20insists%20Paul%20Nixon%2C%20head%20of%20Loch%20Ness%20Center.%20The%20expedition%20is%20the%20most%20elaborate%20in%20the%201300-year%20search%20for%20Nessie%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F25%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Floch-ness-monster-search-timeline.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%20reports.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMany%20have%20speculated%20that%20Nessie%C2%A0is%20a%20dinosaur%20lost%20in%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224853%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20of%20Loch%20Ness%2C%20Scottish%20Highlands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e9c443bc26b400199068ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223639%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EView%20of%20Loch%20Ness%2C%20Scottish%20Highlands%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlongside%20the%20200%20volunteers%20on-site%2C%20almost%20300%20people%20have%20signed%20up%20to%20follow%20a%20livestream%20from%20the%20search%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-scotland-highlands-islands-66614935%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Nixon%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20interest%20in%20our%20weekend%20of%20activities%20has%20been%20fantastic%2C%20and%20to%20see%20how%20people%20worldwide%20are%20still%20fascinated%20by%20the%20story%20of%20the%20loch%20and%20Nessie.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effort%20is%20the%20biggest%20since%201972%2C%20when%20the%20Loch%20Ness%20Investigation%20Bureau%20carried%20out%20a%20study.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20other%20efforts%20to%20find%20Nessie%20have%20persisted.%20In%201987%2C%2024%20boats%20outfitted%20with%20echo%20sounders%20swept%20the%20loch's%20length%20in%20Operation%20Deepscan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20speculated%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FLoch-Ness-monster-legendary-creature%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20creature%20was%20a%20plesiosaur%20dinosaur%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20marine%20reptile%20that%20went%20extinct%2065.5%20million%20years%20ago.%20They%20somehow%20became%20trapped%20in%20Loch%20Ness%20when%20a%20geological%20rupture%20cut%20it%20off%20from%20the%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Floch-ness-monster-real-giant-eel-scientists-say-2019-9%5C%22%3Escientists%20reported%20Nessie%20could%20be%20a%20big%20eel.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20weekend's%20operation%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Quest%2C%26quot%3B%20will%20span%20the%2023-mile-long%20loch.%20Participants%20are%20asked%20to%20document%20everything%20they%20see%20from%20organized%20surface-watched%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20l