jQxLjAuMA..%5C%22%3Ediscriminate%20against%20women.%3C%2Fa%3E%20ChatGPT%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fchatgpt-is-like-many-other-ai-models-rife-with-bias-2023-1%5C%22%3Edemonstrated%20racist%20and%20discriminatory%20biases.%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%C2%A0every%20reported%20case%20of%20police%20misidentifying%20a%20suspect%20because%20of%20facial%20recognition%20technology%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fin-every-reported-false-arrests-based-on-facial-recognition-that-person-has-been-black-2023-8%5C%22%3Ethat%20person%20has%20been%20Black.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2308.02935.pdf%5C%22%3Enew%20research%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20the%20pedestrian%20detection%20software%20in%20self-driving%20cars%20may%20be%20less%20effective%20in%20detecting%20people%20of%20color%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20children%2C%20generally%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20result%20of%20AI%20bias%2C%20putting%20them%20at%20greater%20safety%20risk%20as%20more%20carmakers%20use%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20of%20researchers%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20China%20tested%20how%20well%20eight%20popular%20pedestrian%20detectors%20worked%20depending%20on%20a%20person's%20race%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20age.%20While%20gender%20only%20presented%20a%20small%20discrepancy%20in%20accuracy%2C%20researchers%20found%20the%20detection%20systems%20were%20less%20accurate%20at%20detecting%20pedestrians%20with%20dark%20skin%20tones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%2C%20minority%20individuals%20may%20have%20been%20denied%20vital%20services.%20Now%20they%20might%20face%20severe%20injury%2C%26quot%3B%20Jie%20Zhang%2C%20a%20computer%20scientist%20at%20King's%20College%20London%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20research%20team%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kcl.ac.uk%2Fnews%2Fdriverless-cars-worse-at-detecting-children-and-darker-skinned-pedestrians-say-scientists%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20detection%20systems%20were%2019.67%25%20more%20likely%20to%20detect%20adults%20than%20children%2C%20and%207.52%25%20more%20likely%20to%20detect%20people%20with%20lighter%20skin%20tones%20than%20people%20with%20darker%20skin%20tones%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOverall%2C%20this%20study%20sheds%20light%20on%20the%20fairness%20issues%20faced%20by%20existing%20pedestrian%20detectors%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20importance%20of%20addressing%20bias%20related%20to%20age%20and%20skin%20tone%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20reads.%20%26quot%3BThe%20insights%20gained%20can%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20more%20fair%20and%20unbiased%20autonomous%20driving%20systems%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20trend%20is%20a%20result%20of%20biases%20already%20present%20in%20the%20open-source%20AI%20systems%20that%20many%20companies%20use%20to%20build%20the%20detectors.%20While%20the%20study%20did%20not%20use%20the%20exact%20software%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-full-self-driving-transferrable-for-3-months-amnesty-elon-musk-2023-7%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20like%20Tesla%20use%20to%20power%20self-driving%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20are%20confidential%2C%20the%20software%20systems%20used%20for%20the%20study%20are%20based%20on%20the%20same%20open-source%20AI%20those%20companies%20use%2C%20according%20to%20Zhang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20team%20called%20on%20lawmakers%20to%20regulate%20self-driving%20car%20software%20to%20prevent%20bias%20in%20their%20detection%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20essential%20for%20policymakers%20to%20enact%20laws%20and%20regulations%20that%20safeguard%20the%20rights%20of%20all%20individuals%20and%20address%20these%20concerns%20appropriately%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20reads.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3