%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.ups.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Four-stories%2Fpeople-led%2Fups-to-hire-over-100-000-.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTake%2520UPS%2527s%2520full%252Dtime%2520driver%2Caverage%2520of%2520%252442%2520per%2520hour%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eearn%20about%20%2495%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20after%20they've%20been%20doing%20it%20for%20about%20four%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20earn%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fim-a-ups-delivery-driver-what-my-job-is-like-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrivers%20who%20deliver%20packages%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20we%20work%20more%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20we%20work%20about%2055%20to%2060%20hours%20a%20week.%20The%20average%20package%20delivery%20shift%20is%20eight%20to%2010%20hours.%20Also%2C%20UPS%20pays%20about%20%241%20per%20mile%20for%20some%20routes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20driving%20partner%20and%20I%20are%20on%20the%20road%20for%20five%20days%20at%20a%20time%2C%20driving%20for%2011%20to%2012%20hours%20a%20day%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20route%20I'm%20currently%20on%20pays%20per%20mile%20rather%20than%20hourly.%20Only%20the%20time%20I%20spend%20waiting%20on%20trailers%20and%20doing%20other%20things%20like%20fueling%20up%20or%20washing%20the%20windshield%20periodically%20are%20paid%20by%20the%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20my%20route%2C%20I'm%20paired%20with%20another%20driver%20and%20we%20leave%20on%20Sunday%20mornings.%20We%20drive%20from%20Albuquerque%20to%20Louisville%2C%20Kentucky%3B%20Chicago%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20Dallas%2C%20and%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20bunk%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fari-legacy-sleepers-custom-sleeper-cabs-long-haul-truck-drivers-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeds%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20truck%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20one%20guy%20is%20driving%20his%2011-hour%20shift%2C%20the%20other%20sleeps%20in%20the%20back