t%20lookouts%20over%20four%20years%2C%20but%20often%20people%20will%20get%20one%20lookout%20and%20stay%20there%20for%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20I'm%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2F5-oregon-towns-have-been-substantially-destroyed-by-wildfire-2020-9%5C%22%3Ecentral%20Oregon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20year%2C%20I%20was%20in%20the%20Bob%20Marshall%20Wilderness%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fglacier-national-park-advice-for-planning-the-perfect-vacation-2023-7%5C%22%3EMontana%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20Northern%20Rockies%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20way%20up%20in%20the%20mountains%2C%20and%20they%20brought%20me%20up%20on%20horseback.%20The%20year%20before%2C%20I%20was%20in%20Idaho%2C%20near%20Boise.%20The%20first%20year%2C%20I%20was%20in%20New%20Mexico%2C%20in%20the%20far%20Southern%20Rockies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22869%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mules%20bringing%20supplies%20in%20Montana%20lookout%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e8dc5ebc26b400199006c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22651%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAt%20Malessa's%20lookout%20last%20year%20in%20Montana%2C%20all%20food%2C%20water%2C%20mail%2C%20and%20other%20supplies%20were%20hauled%20in%20by%20pack%20mules%20every%203%20weeks.%3Cp%3EBrig%20Malessa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20in%20a%20cabin%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcamping-over-hotel-stays-near-us-national-parks-2023-3%5C%22%3Eno%20electricity%20or%20running%20water%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20haul%20all%20our%20water%20in%2C%20so%20even%20if%20I%20shower%20it's%20just%20with%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20not%20even%20a%20bucket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weather%20is%20a%20big%20part%20of%20my%20daily%20comfort%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20it%20can%20be%20really%20uncomfortably%20hot%2C%20or%20it%20can%20get%20really%20cold%20or%20wet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lookouts%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-saving-money-on-energy-bills-by-installing-solar-panels-2022-10%5C%22%3Esolar%20panel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20runs%20the%20base%20radio%20for%20work%2C%20and%20connected%20to%20that%20is%20a%20tiny%20inverter%20for%20power.%20I%20also%20have%20my%20own%20solar%20panel%20and%20power%20pack%2C%20and%20as%20long%20as%20I%20remember%20to%20charge%20it%20when%20the%20sun's%20out%2C%20I%20have%20enough%20to%20charge%20my%20phone%2C%20my%20iPad%2C%20and%20my%20other%20camera.%20Some%20places%20will%20provide%20you%20with%20rudimentary%20internet.%20This%20year%2C%20I%20have%20good%20cell%20service%2C%20but%20I%20barely%20had%20any%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brig's%20wash%20basin%20setup%20for%20bathing%20and%20the%20outhouse%20at%20her%20lookout%20in%20Oregon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e8de31b413420019a3942a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20hygiene%2C%20Malessa%20uses%20a%20small%20wash%20basin%20for%20bathing.%20Her%20Oregon%20lookout%20is%20equipped%20with%20an%20outhouse.%3Cp%3EBrig%20Malessa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pay%20is%20%2418.06%20an%20hour.%20In%20this%20district%20we%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20overtime%20%E2%80%94%20I%20work%20seven%20days%20a%20week%2C%2012%20hour%20days%2C%20even%20more%20if%20there's%20a%20fire.%20Last%20summer%2C%20I%20brought%20home%20around%20%2411%2C000%2C%20and%20I'll%20probably%20double%20that%20this%20year.%20I'm%20at%20this%20location%20from%20the%20end%20of%20May%20to%20the%20middle%20of%20October%2C%20which%20is%20fairly%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20really%20was%20no%20formal%20training%20for%20me%2C%20though%20it's%20different%20everywhere.%20If%20you're%20a%20wildland%20firefighter%20you're%20definitely%20going%20to%20be%20a%20better%20fire%20lookout%20to%20start%2C%20but%20it's%20something%20anybody%20can%20learn.%20If%20you're%20observant%20and%20proactive%2C%20you'll%20figure%20it%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20health%20requirements%2C%20your%20vision%20and%20hearing%20just%20need%20to%20be%20correctable%20enough%20to%20do%20the%20job.%20You%20should%20be%20able%20to%20read%20and%20write%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20get%20up%20a%20flight%20of%20stairs.%20That's%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20think%20I%20spot%20smoke%20the%20very%20first%20thing%20I%20do%20is%20glance%20at%20the%20clock%20and%20write%20down%20the%20time.%20Then%20I%20go%20for%20my%20binoculars%20and%20start%20watching%20it%20until%20I'm%20sure%20it's%20smoke.%20Sometimes%20I%20know%20that%20it's%20smoke%20within%20a%20second%2C%20but%20sometimes%20I%20don't%20know%20for%20sure.%20It%20could%20be%20weird%20clouds%2C%20or%20it%20could%20be%20dust.%20As%20time%20goes%20on%20you%20learn%20to%20pick%20out%20what's%20smoke%20and%20what's%20not%20pretty%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20go%20to%20the%20Osborne%20Fire%20Finder%2C%20which%20is%20the%20main%20tool%20we%20use.%20I%20find%20an%20azimuth%2C%20which%20is%20the%20direction%20of%20a%20fire%20from%20where%20I'm%20standing%20in%20degrees%2C%20and%20then%20start%20whittling%20down%20where%20and%20how%20far%20away%20it%20is.%20I%20call%20dispatch%20and%20tell%20them%20the%20azimuth%2C%20the%20distance%2C%20the%20behavior%20of%20the%20fire%2C%20a%20description%20of%20the%20smoke%20that%20I'm%20seeing%2C%20and%20the%20fuel%20that%20might%20be%20burning.%20Depending%20on%20where%20you%20are%2C%20they%20usually%20send%20out%20a%20plane%20to%20confirm%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20main%20tools%20of%20the%20fire%20lookout%20job%20are%20a%20radio%20and%20the%20Osborne%20Fire%20Finder.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e8e270b413420019a39a71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20main%20tools%20of%20the%20fire%20lookout%20job%20are%20a%20radio%20and%20the%20Osborne%20Fire%20Finder.%3Cp%3EBrig%20Malessa%2C%20Sophie%20Vernholm%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20see%20the%20biggest%20viewshed%20possible.%20For%20me%2C%20right%20now%20that's%20upstairs%20in%20my%2014-by-14%20foot%20room.%20I%20can%20take%20a%20walk%20and%20just%20carry%20my%20radio%20with%20me%2C%20but%20I%20only%20go%20downstairs%20for%20a%20maximum%20of%2030%20minutes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20I'm%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20not%20scanning%20100%25%20of%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20you%20just%20make%20sure%20to%20take%20a%20good%20360%20every%2015%20to%2020%20minutes%2C%20which%20might%20take%20two%20minutes.%20Once%20you%20get%20used%20to%20it%2C%20you're%20always%20kind%20of%20watching.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20do%20anything%20you%20want%20as%20long%20as%20you're%20keeping%20an%20eye%20out.%20This%20job%20is%20historically%20well-loved%20by%20artists%2C%20musicians%2C%20and%20writers.%20A%20lot%20of%20big%20writers%20have%20been%20fire%20lookouts%20%E2%80%94%20Jack%20Kerouac%2C%20Edward%20Abbey%2C%20Gary%20Snyder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20lots%20of%20little%20creative%20things.%20I%20do%20artwork%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20to%20play%20the%20ukulele.%20This%20year%2C%20I%20got%20a%20bow%2C%20and%20I'm%20trying%20archery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brig%20uses%20her%20time%20to%20explore%20creative%20pursuits%2C%20like%20music%20and%20art.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e8df5dbc26b40019900bf2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMalessa%20uses%20her%20time%20to%20explore%20creative%20pursuits%2C%20like%20music%20and%20art.%3Cp%3EBrig%20Malessa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20see%20other%20people%20at%20least%20every%20few%20weeks.%20People%20are%20welcome%