By%20May%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20to%20Netaji%20that%20the%20war%20in%20the%20eastern%20hemisphere%20was%20coming%20to%20its%20logical%20end.%20He%20decided%20with%20his%20inner%20Council%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20on%20May%2017%20in%20Bangkok%2C%20to%20switch%20over%20to%20underground%20activity%20operating%20from%20Indian%20soil.%20Directives%20were%20issued%20to%20the%20armed%20forces%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Army%20(INA)%20and%20to%20the%20Indian%20Independence%20League%20(IIL)%20to%20start%20moving%20clandestinely%20towards%20India%20for%20an%20armed%20revolution.%20He%20planned%20to%20involve%20the%20demobilised%20British%20army%20men%2C%20industrial%20workers%20of%20Ordinance%20factories%2C%20the%20peasants%20who%20suffered%20from%20the%20war%2C%20and%20political%20workers%20especially%20those%20having%20a%20leftist%20tendency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetaji%20himself%20was%20to%20return%20to%20Indian%20soil.%20It%20was%20decided%20that%20he%20would%20be%20dropped%20somewhere%20in%20Assam%20or%20Bengal.%20In%20case%20that%20was%20not%20possible%20directly%2C%20he%20was%20to%20proceed%20to%20Yunan%2C%20China%2C%20near%20the%20Burmese%20border%20from%20where%20he%20could%20slip%20into%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25163915%2Fbose-11.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22631%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25163915%2Fbose-11.jpg%20631w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25163915%2Fbose-11-300x253.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669825%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENetaji%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20India%3A%20Debnath%20Das%2C%20GS%2C%20IIL%20Hq%20East%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDebnath%20Das%2C%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20IIL%2C%20remained%20the%20closest%20to%20Netaji%20during%20this%20period.%20Das%20was%20with%20him%20from%20January%20onwards%20in%20Burma%20and%20during%20the%20crucial%20months%20of%20May-July%20in%20Bangkok%20when%20Netaji%20was%20chalking%20out%20plans%20for%20post-Japan%E2%80%99s%20inevitable%20defeat.%20Das%20was%20the%20co-founder%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Indian%20National%20Council%E2%80%99%20set%20up%20in%20Bangkok%20in%20December%201941.%20He%20was%20the%20secretary%20when%20Rashbehari%20Bose%20was%20the%20president.%20He%20had%20the%20background%20of%20being%20a%20member%20of%20the%20underground%20revolutionary%20teams%20of%20Jugantar%20and%20Anushilon%20Samity.%20Das%20was%20appointed%20to%20head%20the%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJapan%E2%80%99s%20surrender%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetaji%20hurriedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fnetaji-subhas-chandra-bose-japan-plane-crash%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520spite%2520of%2520administering%2520stimulants%2C%2527Chandra%2520Bose%2527%2520in%2520Japanese.%5C%22%3Ereturned%20to%20Singapore%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20August%2013%20after%20being%20informed%20of%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20surrender.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20emergency.%20The%20discussion%20at%20his%20house%20with%20all%20available%20military%20and%20civil%20chiefs%20continued%20throughout%20August%2014%20till%20the%20morning%20of%20August%2015.%C2%A0It%20was%20decided%20that%20the%20Army%20would%20surrender%20as%20a%20separate%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fstill-hidden-after-all-these-years-indias-official-history-of-the-ina-and-japans-netaji-files%5C%22%3EStill%20Hidden%20After%20All%20These%20Years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Official%20History%20of%20the%20INA%20and%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20Netaji%20Files%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20members%20suggested%20that%20Netaji%20should%20leave%20Singapore%20and%20go%20away%20to%20some%20other%20safer%20place%20as%20the%20Allies%20would%20adopt%20a%20very%20vindictive%20attitude%20towards%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetaji%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo!%E2%80%9D%20He%20was%20prepared%20to%20face%20the%20consequences%20with%20his%20other%20colleagues.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20worst%20they%20can%20do%20is%20to%20put%20me%20against%20the%20wall%20and%20shoot%20me%20and%20I%20am%20prepared%20for%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20strong%20suggestion%20that%20Netaji%20should%20not%20stay%20in%20Singapore%2C%20it%20was%20ultimately%20decided%20that%20he%20would%20stay%20there%20as%20he%20could%20not%20look%20for%20protection%20or%20help%20from%20any%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20the%20day%2C%20Sarkar%2C%20legal%20adviser%2C%20who%20arrived%20from%20Bangkok%2C%20informed%20that%20General%20Isoda%2C%20Chief%20of%20the%20Japanese%20Liaison%20office%20attached%20to%20the%20Azad%20Hind%20Government%20in%20Bangkok%2C%20and%20Hachiya%2C%20Japanese%20Minister-designate%20to%20the%20Provisional%20Government%20of%20Azad%20Hind%2C%20were%20keen%20to%20render%20whatever%20service%20they%20could%20in%20Netaji%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20get%20away%20from%20Malaya%20and%20Siam%20so%20that%20he%20would%20not%20fall%20a%20prisoner%20in%20Anglo-American%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetaji%20decided%20to%20leave%20for%20Bangkok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20Bangkok%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20arrival%20in%20Bangkok%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20August%2016%2C%20before%20going%20to%20the%20IIL%20Headquarters%2C%20Netaji%20sat%20with%20the%20Japanese%20liaison%20officers%20at%20the%20residence%20of%20Isoda%20for%20the%20next%20stage%20of%20action.%20Isoda%20offered%20Netaji%20four%20alternatives%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENetaji%20fly%20to%20Tokyo%20and%20seek%20shelter%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESurrender%20with%20his%20force%20in%20Bangkok%20to%20Lord%20Mountbatten%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFly%20to%20Manila%20and%20surrender%20to%20General%20McArthur%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EProceed%20to%20Manchuria%20to%20join%20Russians%20who%20have%20occupied%20the%20area%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDropping%20Netaji%20somewhere%20in%20Assam%20or%20Bengal%20was%20totally%20out%20of%20their%20consideration.%20Netaji%20was%20compelled%20to%20choose%20the%20fourth%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20alternative%20choices%20were%20an%20eyewash%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20deposition%20made%20by%20Col.%20Yano%20who%20was%20present%20in%20the%20meeting%20Isoda%20had%20with%20Field%20Marshal%20Count%20Terauchi%20the%20previous%20night.%20It%20was%20arranged%20such%20that%20Netaji%20would%20arrive%20at%20Saigon%20and%20they%20would%20take%20Bose%20to%20Tokyo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELate%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20Netaji%20called%20a%20meeting%20of%20all%20officers%20at%20his%20residence.%20There%2C%20he%20announced%20his%20decision%20to%20leave%20Bangkok%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Cadventure%20into%20the%20unknown%E2%80%9D%20with%20S.A.%20Ayer%2C%20Debnath%20Das%2C%20Colonel%20Habibur%20Rahman%2C%20Captain%20Gulzara%20Singh%2C%20Colonel%20Pritam%20Singh%2C%20and%20Major%20Abid%20Hasan%2C%20to%20continue%20the%20struggle%20for%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20left%20Bangkok%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20of%20August%2017%2C%20for%20Saigon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20to%3F%20India%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetaji%20never%20disclosed%20to%20any%20of%20his%20colleagues%20where%20he%20was%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Debnath%20Das%20gave%20detailed%20information%20on%20Netaji%E2%80%99s%20plans.%20Das%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20Netaji%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20go%20to%20India%20and%20continue%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20liberation%20fight%20from%20some%20underground%20centre.%20Japan%20agreed%20to%20take%20Netaji%20from%20Bangkok%20to%20somewhere%20in%20Bengal%20and%20agreed%20to%20take%20responsibility%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20%E2%80%9Con%20this%20understanding%2C%20Netaji%20emplaned%20for%20Saigon%2C%20as%20according%20to%20the%20Japanese%2C%20it%20could%20have%20been%20easier%20for%20him%20and%20his%20officers%20to%20go%20to%20India%20through%20Saigon%2C%20as%20there%20was%20less%20vigilance%20of%20the%20Allied%20forces%20on%20that%20route.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25164008%2Fbose-12.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22905%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25164008%2Fbose-12.jpg%20905w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25164008%2Fbose-12-300x158.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669826%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22476%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIt%20was%20Netaji%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20go%20to%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20Saigon%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20arrival%20at%20Saigon%2C%20while%20Netaji%20and%20his%20team%20were%20taking%20their%20much-needed%20rest%2C%20Isoda%20and%20Hachiya%20went%20up%20to%20Netaji%E2%80%99s%20room.%20Netaji%20immediately%20came%20out%20and%20woke%20up%20Debhath%20Das%20in%20the%20next%20room.%20He%20exclaimed%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20see!%20They%20are%20changing%20the%20Plan%20%E2%80%93%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20why%20%E2%80%93%20I%20think%20they%20are%20now%20taking%20me%20to%20Tokyo%20%E2%80%93%20just%20come%20and%20have%20a%20talk%20with%20General%20Isoda.%E2%80%9D%20He%20asked%20Debnath%20to%20call%20all%20the%20other%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20all%20came%20and%20vehemently%20opposed%20Isoda%E2%80%99s%20plan.%20Debnath%20demanded%20that%20there%20should%20be%20no%20change%20in%20the%20plan%20and%20Netaji%20must%20be%20taken%20to%20India.%20The%20logical%20reason%20is%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceven%20if%20we%20are%20captured%2C%20the%20people%20will%20come%20to%20know%20and%20help%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20478px)%2085vw%2C%20478px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25164053%2Fbose-13.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22478%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25164053%2Fbose-13.jpg%20478w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F25164053%2Fbose-13-249x300.jpg%20249w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669827%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAt%20Saigon%2C%20Japan%20changed%20the%20plan%20and%20took%20Netaji%20to%20Tokyo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20resented%20the%20idea%20of%20giving%20only%20one%20seat%20to%20Netaji.%20Isoda%20explained%20that%20it%20was%20not%20possible%20to%20get%20a%20separate%20plane%20for%20the%20party%20because%20of%20the%20flying%20restrictions%20imposed%20by%20the%20Allied%20forces.%20But%20as%20one%20plane%20is%20on%20the%20way%20to%20Tokyo%2C%20Netaji%20could%20be%20accommodated%20there.%20A%20bit%20later%20he%20agreed%20to%20give%20one%20more%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20felt%20helpless%20at%20the%20new%20move%2C%20so%20surprisingly%20made%20at%20Saigon%20where%20they%20were%20placed%20at%20the%20most%20disadvantageous%20position%2C%20far%20away%20from%20their%20own%20armed%20forces%20stationed%20in%20Bangkok%2C%20Singapore%2C%20and%20Moulmein.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20even%20pleaded%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20there%20are%20unimportant%20Japanese%20personnel%2C%20why%2C%20General%2C%20you%20do%20not%20ask%20them%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20next%20plane%3B%20let%20us%20all%20go%20together.%E2%80%9D%20Isoda%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20not%20know%20yet.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20team%20reached%20the%20aerodrome%2C%20they%20found%20the%20plane%20almost%20on%20the%20move.%20The%20plane%20was%20an%20old%20heavy%20bomber%20Mitsubishi%20Ki%2021.%20It%20came%20from%20Singapore%20and%20had%2011%20Japanese%20army%20men%20on%20board%20including%20General%20Shidei%2C%20Chief%20of%20the%20General%20Staff%20in%20Burma%2C%20on%20transfer%20to%20Manchuria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahman%20wondered%20why%20Isoda%20and%20Hachiya%20did%20not%20accompany%20Netaji%20to%20Tokyo.%20According%20to%20Debnath%2C%20Isoda%20was%20among%20those%20instrumental%20in%20effecting%20the%20change%20in%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plane%20took%20off%20late%20in%20the%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENetaji%20switched%20plans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECajoled%20and%20forced%20to%20board%20a%20flight%20to%20Tokyo%20leaving%20his%20team%20stranded%20at%20Saigon%2C%20Netaji%20decided%20to%20get%20down%20at%20Dairen%20along%20with%20Genl.%20Shidei.%20From%20there%2C%20he%20would%20journey%20to%20Mukuden%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20Manchuria.%20It%20would%20have%20served%20no%20purpose%20to%20him%20for%20continuing%20the%20flight%20to%20Japan%20which%20had%20already%20surrendered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20really%20happened%20at%20Taihoku%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20sooner%20the%20plane%20was%20airborne%2C%20at%20about%20an%20altitude%20of%2020-30%20metres%2C%20there%20was%20the%20sound%20of%20an%20explosion%20followed%20by%20three%20to%20four%20loud%20bangs.%20The%20left%20engine%20fell%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahman%20recorded%2C%20%E2%80%9CSuddenly%20I%20heard%20a%20deafening%20noise%20as%20if%20some%20cannon%20shell%20had%20hit%20the%20starboard%20side%20of%20the%20plane.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20452px)%2085vw%2C%20452p